In Java, you can return multiple variables by creating a custom class or by using an array or collection. Here are some examples:

1. Creating a custom class:

You can create a custom class that contains all the variables you want to return. Here's an example:

```
public class MyVariables {
  private int variable1;
  private String variable2;

  public MyVariables(int variable1, String variable2) {
    this.variable1 = variable1;
    this.variable2 = variable2;
  }

  public int getVariable1() {
    return variable1;
  }

  public String getVariable2() {
    return variable2;
  }
}
```

You can then create an instance of this class and return it:

```
public MyVariables myMethod() {
  int variable1 = 1;
  String variable2 = "two";

  return new MyVariables(variable1, variable2);
}
```

2. Using an array:

You can also use an array to return multiple variables. Here's an example:

```
public int[] myMethod() {
  int variable1 = 1;
  int variable2 = 2;
  int variable3 = 3;

  return new int[] { variable1, variable2, variable3 };
}
